reviewText: This was bought as a nostalgia type gift.  It is a mix of cartoons, but overall it is a neat little collection of Nick Toons.  7 episodes: The Finster Who Stole Christmas (All Grown Up); Christmas Who? (SpongeBob SquarePants); Christmas Every Day! (The Fairly OddParents); The Santa Experience (Rugrats); The Fright Before Christmas! (Danny Phantom); A Robot for All Seasons (My Life as a Teenage Robot); When Santas Collide (ChalkZone).  Just under 3 hours long will keep kids busy watching the stuff you grew up on.
Title: N/A

reviewText: I bought it for 3 episodes: Christmas Who? (SpongeBob SquarePants), Christmas Every Day! (The Fairly OddParents), and The Santa Experience (Rugrats). The quality is good and the price was great. (I only wish it included the Christmas episodes of Rocko's Modern Life, Doug, and Hey Arnold!) But for the price, even if you only like a couple of these cartoons, it is well worth the price.
Title: N/A

reviewText: I can't tell you how many times we've watched this DVD or certain episodes of it.  We absolutely love it. Includes SpongeBob's first Christmas, All Grown Up when Chuckie accidentally steals someones tree that he thought was discarded, the episode where Timmy Turner wishes for it to be Christmas every day, and other neat Nick holiday shows.Definitely a great buy if your kids watch Nick!
Title: N/A

reviewText: This DVD has Chalk Zone in it. There haven't been that many episodes of Chalk Zone released lately. Someone should leave a message or note about releasing more Chalk Zone episodes onto DVD evan if there's gonna be a DVD of the first season. Chalk Zone is such a great show.
summary: More Chalk Zone episodes should be released on DVD
